# SSH allowed-signers file consumed by `ssh-keygen -Y verify` and by
# redteam.auth.SignatureVerifier. One operator per line:
#
#   <principal> [namespaces="redteam-engagement"] <ssh-public-key>
#
# Or, for an SSH-CA-backed setup:
#
#   <principal> cert-authority namespaces="redteam-engagement" <ssh-ca-public-key>
#
# Rotation = a PR that adds/removes a line. The file is read at engagement
# parse time on the operator workstation AND inside the container during
# `redteam run`.
#
# alice@example.com namespaces="redteam-engagement" ssh-ed25519 AAAA... alice@laptop
